Package com.safenar.math

Interface Generator

All Known Implementing Classes:
FibonacciGenerator, Generators
Functional Interface:
This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
@FunctionalInterface public interface Generator
A Generator is a function by which sequences are generated.

    • hash

      default int hash()
      Deprecated.
      hash code from this implementation remains the same for the same Generator across different executions, which collides with first point of the Object.hashCode()
      Use this instead of Object.hashCode()
      Returns:
      hash of this Generator
      Implementation Note:
      indexes of the values are between -5 and 5, both inclusive

    • string

      default String string()
      Use this instead of Object.toString()
      Returns:
      string representation of this Generator
      Implementation Requirements:
      since there's no simple way to get the equation this Generator represents, we just generate values for indexes between -5 and 5
